title: Millburn High School girls tennis players advance
text:
Millburn High School girls tennis players advance October 8, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 8, 2015, 12:31 AM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills 
Six members of Millburn High School’s varsity girls tennis team remain in contention for New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association singles and doubles championships. 
Stephanie Schrage and Alex Pritsker have reached the third round of the state singles tournament. 
Schrage, the 2014 state singles runner-up, is the top seed. Pritsker is an alphabetical 17-28 seed. 
Both Schrage and Pritsker are scheduled to play their third-round matches in the rain delayed tournament Saturday, Oct. 10, at Mercer County Park in West Windsor. 
The scheduled Oct. 3 start to the tournament was rained out, postponing the opening two rounds of play to the following day. 
Fourth round play also is scheduled to take place on Oct. 10. The quarterfinals and semifinals are set for the following day, Oct. 11 at the same venue. 
Top-seeded Isabella Waung and Sydney Zirlin are scheduled to play their second round doubles tournament match Oct. 10 at Veterans Park in Hamilton Township. 
The unseeded duo of Elizabeth Gray and Anna Mandel also are set to play their second round match that day. 
Third round play also takes place on Oct. 10. 
The quarterfinals and semifinals, due to the Oct. 3 rainout, are now scheduled for Oct. 11 at Mercer County Park. 
The finals of the singles and doubles tournaments are set for Saturday, Oct. 17, at Mercer County Park. 
-Jim Connelly © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
